article.headline: Dartmouth 63, Brown 61
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Dan Biber hit a clutch free throw with 11 seconds left, his only point, to help Dartmouth beat Brown 63-61 in overtime Friday night. Brown had two more chances, but Robby Pride stole the ball with 2.8 seconds left, was fouled and hit a free throw for the final score. Alex Barnett had 28 points to lead Dartmouth ( 5-14, 3-2 Ivy League). He forced the overtime with a 3-pointer that tied it 55-55 with just under a minute left. Scott Friske had 19 points and 13 rebounds and Peter Sullivan added 18 points for Brown (6-13, 0-5). The Bears turned the ball over on three of their last four possessions. Brown led 59-57, but Marlon Sanders tied it with two free throws and Pride drove for a layup. Matt Mullery tied it for the Bears at 61 with 48 seconds left. The Big Green won two in a row for the first time this season.
